data.name: TextBox1.Text
data.value:
- A tyre is circular in shape and made up of a core of wires and cords, surrounded by an outer rubber tread which is inflated with compressed air.
- A car wheel is composed of a solid inner which is welded on to an outer rim.
- The tyre complete set fit on to the wheel rim of each wheel, covering and protecting the rim, while providing a vital cushioned structure to make contact with the surface of the road.
